lie bumps wat are lie bumps these painful red or white bumps on the tongue are called transient lingual papillitis in m d speak they're called lie bumps in the south because of an old tale that telling a whopper would bring one on the true culprit sharp or crusty foods that cause teeth to scrape the tongue's papillae or taste buds the papillae will heal on their own in a few days but you can ease the pain with otc protective gels such as orabase or zilactin b says carl allen d d s director of oral and maxillofacial pathology at the ohio state university's college of dentistry Tongue Dentistry Halitosis Tooth Fluoride therapy Oral and maxillofacial surgery Mouth ulcer Tooth enamel Leaf Aloe Dental caries Cat Pathology Breastfeeding Medicine Skin Wisdom teeth Glossitis Bumps race Tooth development Angkor Wat Oral sex Earthsea Hiberno-English The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Diclofenac Group A streptococcal infection Trumpet Sensation Pentecostalism The University of Texas Health Science Center at San Antonio Dental brace Wound healing phases Kawasaki disease Bruise Tongue piercing Herpes simplex virus Basic taste Guinea pig Minor characters in Teen Titans (animated series) Son Goku (Dragon Ball) The Amber Spyglass Osteoarthritis Kidney Cocaine Taste Body piercing Buddhism Baylor College of Dentistry Bray Productions Terri Schiavo Sea urchin Domestic rabbit Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Hypnosis Lent Bumps Essential oil CBS Oral cancer Ohio State University Paracetamol Gospel of Thomas Methamphetamine Multiple sclerosis University of Indonesia Foie gras Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an A. A. Allen Narcissism J. R. R. Tolkien Happy Tree Friends Strap-on dildo Plame affair Characters of Naruto Stomach cancer Trapping Erythronium Novel Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Actinic keratosis Explosive material Hannibal Lecter Sunburn Manner of articulation Glossary of medical terms related to communications disorders Psoriasis Tyrannosaurus rex RuneScape quests Ala